76bool RequiresEncoderReset(const VideoCodec& prev_send_codec,
77 const VideoCodec& new_send_codec,
78 bool was_encode_called_since_last_initialization) {
79 // Does not check max/minBitrate or maxFramerate.
80 if (new_send_codec.codecType != prev_send_codec.codecType ||
81 new_send_codec.width != prev_send_codec.width ||
82 new_send_codec.height != prev_send_codec.height ||
83 new_send_codec.qpMax != prev_send_codec.qpMax ||
84 new_send_codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams !=
85 prev_send_codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams ||
86 new_send_codec.mode != prev_send_codec.mode) {
87 return true;
88 }
89
90 if (!was_encode_called_since_last_initialization &&
91 (new_send_codec.startBitrate != prev_send_codec.startBitrate)) {
92 // If start bitrate has changed reconfigure encoder only if encoding had not
93 // yet started.
94 return true;
95 }
96
97 switch (new_send_codec.codecType) {
98 case kVideoCodecVP8:
99 if (new_send_codec.VP8() != prev_send_codec.VP8()) {
100 return true;
101 }
102 break;
103
104 case kVideoCodecVP9:
105 if (new_send_codec.VP9() != prev_send_codec.VP9()) {
106 return true;
107 }
108 break;
109
110 case kVideoCodecH264:
111 if (new_send_codec.H264() != prev_send_codec.H264()) {
112 return true;
113 }
114 break;
115
116 default:
117 break;
118 }
119
120 for (unsigned char i = 0; i < new_send_codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams; ++i) {
121 if (!new_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].active) {
122 // No need to reset when stream is inactive.
123 continue;
124 }
125
126 if (!prev_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].active ||
127 new_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].width !=
128 prev_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].width ||
129 new_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].height !=
130 prev_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].height ||
131 new_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].numberOfTemporalLayers !=
132 prev_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].numberOfTemporalLayers ||
133 new_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].qpMax !=
134 prev_send_codec.simulcastStream[i].qpMax) {
135 return true;
136 }
137 }
138
139 if (new_send_codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
140 size_t num_spatial_layers = new_send_codec.VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers;
141 for (unsigned char i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers; ++i) {
142 if (new_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].width !=
143 prev_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].width ||
144 new_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].height !=
145 prev_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].height ||
146 new_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].numberOfTemporalLayers !=
147 prev_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].numberOfTemporalLayers ||
148 new_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].qpMax !=
149 prev_send_codec.spatialLayers[i].qpMax) {
150 return true;
151 }
152 }
153 }
154
155 if (new_send_codec.ScalabilityMode() != prev_send_codec.ScalabilityMode()) {
156 return true;
157 }
158
159 return false;
160}

162std::array<uint8_t, 2> GetExperimentGroups() {
163 std::array<uint8_t, 2> experiment_groups;
164 absl::optional<AlrExperimentSettings> experiment_settings =
165 AlrExperimentSettings::CreateFromFieldTrial(
166 AlrExperimentSettings::kStrictPacingAndProbingExperimentName);
167 if (experiment_settings) {
168 experiment_groups[0] = experiment_settings->group_id + 1;
169 } else {
170 experiment_groups[0] = 0;
171 }
172 experiment_settings = AlrExperimentSettings::CreateFromFieldTrial(
173 AlrExperimentSettings::kScreenshareProbingBweExperimentName);
174 if (experiment_settings) {
175 experiment_groups[1] = experiment_settings->group_id + 1;
176 } else {
177 experiment_groups[1] = 0;
178 }
179 return experiment_groups;
180}

182// Limit allocation across TLs in bitrate allocation according to number of TLs
183// in EncoderInfo.
184VideoBitrateAllocation UpdateAllocationFromEncoderInfo(
185 const VideoBitrateAllocation& allocation,
186 const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& encoder_info) {
187 if (allocation.get_sum_bps() == 0) {
188 return allocation;
189 }
190 VideoBitrateAllocation new_allocation;
191 for (int si = 0; si < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++si) {
192 if (encoder_info.fps_allocation[si].size() == 1 &&
193 allocation.IsSpatialLayerUsed(si)) {
194 // One TL is signalled to be used by the encoder. Do not distribute
195 // bitrate allocation across TLs (use sum at ti:0).
196 new_allocation.SetBitrate(si, 0, allocation.GetSpatialLayerSum(si));
197 } else {
198 for (int ti = 0; ti < kMaxTemporalStreams; ++ti) {
199 if (allocation.HasBitrate(si, ti))
200 new_allocation.SetBitrate(si, ti, allocation.GetBitrate(si, ti));
201 }
202 }
203 }
204 new_allocation.set_bw_limited(allocation.is_bw_limited());
205 return new_allocation;
206}

208// Converts a VideoBitrateAllocation that contains allocated bitrate per layer,
209// and an EncoderInfo that contains information about the actual encoder
210// structure used by a codec. Stream structures can be Ksvc, Full SVC, Simulcast
211// etc.
212VideoLayersAllocation CreateVideoLayersAllocation(
213 const VideoCodec& encoder_config,
214 const VideoEncoder::RateControlParameters& current_rate,
215 const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& encoder_info) {
216 const VideoBitrateAllocation& target_bitrate = current_rate.target_bitrate;
217 VideoLayersAllocation layers_allocation;
218 if (target_bitrate.get_sum_bps() == 0) {
219 return layers_allocation;
220 }
221
222 if (encoder_config.numberOfSimulcastStreams > 1) {
223 layers_allocation.resolution_and_frame_rate_is_valid = true;
224 for (int si = 0; si < encoder_config.numberOfSimulcastStreams; ++si) {
225 if (!target_bitrate.IsSpatialLayerUsed(si) ||
226 target_bitrate.GetSpatialLayerSum(si) == 0) {
227 continue;
228 }
229 layers_allocation.active_spatial_layers.emplace_back();
230 VideoLayersAllocation::SpatialLayer& spatial_layer =
231 layers_allocation.active_spatial_layers.back();
232 spatial_layer.width = encoder_config.simulcastStream[si].width;
233 spatial_layer.height = encoder_config.simulcastStream[si].height;
234 spatial_layer.rtp_stream_index = si;
235 spatial_layer.spatial_id = 0;
236 auto frame_rate_fraction =
237 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::kMaxFramerateFraction;
238 if (encoder_info.fps_allocation[si].size() == 1) {
239 // One TL is signalled to be used by the encoder. Do not distribute
240 // bitrate allocation across TLs (use sum at tl:0).
241 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
242 DataRate::BitsPerSec(target_bitrate.GetSpatialLayerSum(si)));
243 frame_rate_fraction = encoder_info.fps_allocation[si][0];
244 } else { // Temporal layers are supported.
245 uint32_t temporal_layer_bitrate_bps = 0;
246 for (size_t ti = 0;
247 ti < encoder_config.simulcastStream[si].numberOfTemporalLayers;
248 ++ti) {
249 if (!target_bitrate.HasBitrate(si, ti)) {
250 break;
251 }
252 if (ti < encoder_info.fps_allocation[si].size()) {
253 // Use frame rate of the top used temporal layer.
254 frame_rate_fraction = encoder_info.fps_allocation[si][ti];
255 }
256 temporal_layer_bitrate_bps += target_bitrate.GetBitrate(si, ti);
257 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
258 DataRate::BitsPerSec(temporal_layer_bitrate_bps));
259 }
260 }
261 // Encoder may drop frames internally if `maxFramerate` is set.
262 spatial_layer.frame_rate_fps = std::min<uint8_t>(
263 encoder_config.simulcastStream[si].maxFramerate,
264 rtc::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(
265 (current_rate.framerate_fps * frame_rate_fraction) /
266 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::kMaxFramerateFraction));
267 }
268 } else if (encoder_config.numberOfSimulcastStreams == 1) {
269 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/12000): Implement support for AV1 with
270 // scalability.
271 const bool higher_spatial_depend_on_lower =
272 encoder_config.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9 &&
273 encoder_config.VP9().interLayerPred == InterLayerPredMode::kOn;
274 layers_allocation.resolution_and_frame_rate_is_valid = true;
275
276 std::vector<DataRate> aggregated_spatial_bitrate(
277 webrtc::kMaxTemporalStreams, DataRate::Zero());
278 for (int si = 0; si < webrtc::kMaxSpatialLayers; ++si) {
279 layers_allocation.resolution_and_frame_rate_is_valid = true;
280 if (!target_bitrate.IsSpatialLayerUsed(si) ||
281 target_bitrate.GetSpatialLayerSum(si) == 0) {
282 break;
283 }
284 layers_allocation.active_spatial_layers.emplace_back();
285 VideoLayersAllocation::SpatialLayer& spatial_layer =
286 layers_allocation.active_spatial_layers.back();
287 spatial_layer.width = encoder_config.spatialLayers[si].width;
288 spatial_layer.height = encoder_config.spatialLayers[si].height;
289 spatial_layer.rtp_stream_index = 0;
290 spatial_layer.spatial_id = si;
291 auto frame_rate_fraction =
292 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::kMaxFramerateFraction;
293 if (encoder_info.fps_allocation[si].size() == 1) {
294 // One TL is signalled to be used by the encoder. Do not distribute
295 // bitrate allocation across TLs (use sum at tl:0).
296 DataRate aggregated_temporal_bitrate =
297 DataRate::BitsPerSec(target_bitrate.GetSpatialLayerSum(si));
298 aggregated_spatial_bitrate[0] += aggregated_temporal_bitrate;
299 if (higher_spatial_depend_on_lower) {
300 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
301 aggregated_spatial_bitrate[0]);
302 } else {
303 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
304 aggregated_temporal_bitrate);
305 }
306 frame_rate_fraction = encoder_info.fps_allocation[si][0];
307 } else { // Temporal layers are supported.
308 DataRate aggregated_temporal_bitrate = DataRate::Zero();
309 for (size_t ti = 0;
310 ti < encoder_config.spatialLayers[si].numberOfTemporalLayers;
311 ++ti) {
312 if (!target_bitrate.HasBitrate(si, ti)) {
313 break;
314 }
315 if (ti < encoder_info.fps_allocation[si].size()) {
316 // Use frame rate of the top used temporal layer.
317 frame_rate_fraction = encoder_info.fps_allocation[si][ti];
318 }
319 aggregated_temporal_bitrate +=
320 DataRate::BitsPerSec(target_bitrate.GetBitrate(si, ti));
321 if (higher_spatial_depend_on_lower) {
322 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
323 aggregated_temporal_bitrate + aggregated_spatial_bitrate[ti]);
324 aggregated_spatial_bitrate[ti] += aggregated_temporal_bitrate;
325 } else {
326 spatial_layer.target_bitrate_per_temporal_layer.push_back(
327 aggregated_temporal_bitrate);
328 }
329 }
330 }
331 // Encoder may drop frames internally if `maxFramerate` is set.
332 spatial_layer.frame_rate_fps = std::min<uint8_t>(
333 encoder_config.spatialLayers[si].maxFramerate,
334 rtc::saturated_cast<uint8_t>(
335 (current_rate.framerate_fps * frame_rate_fraction) /
336 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo::kMaxFramerateFraction));
337 }
338 }
339
340 return layers_allocation;
341}

343VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo GetEncoderInfoWithBitrateLimitUpdate(
344 const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& info,
345 const VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config,
346 bool default_limits_allowed) {
347 if (!default_limits_allowed || !info.resolution_bitrate_limits.empty() ||
348 encoder_config.simulcast_layers.size() <= 1) {
349 return info;
350 }
351 // Bitrate limits are not configured and more than one layer is used, use
352 // the default limits (bitrate limits are not used for simulcast).
353 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo new_info = info;
354 new_info.resolution_bitrate_limits =
355 EncoderInfoSettings::GetDefaultSinglecastBitrateLimits(
356 encoder_config.codec_type);
357 return new_info;
358}

360int NumActiveStreams(const std::vector<VideoStream>& streams) {
361 int num_active = 0;
362 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
363 if (stream.active)
364 ++num_active;
365 }
366 return num_active;
367}

369void ApplyVp9BitrateLimits(const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& encoder_info,
370 const VideoEncoderConfig& encoder_config,
371 VideoCodec* codec) {
372 if (codec->codecType != VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP9 ||
373 encoder_config.simulcast_layers.size() <= 1 ||
374 VideoStreamEncoderResourceManager::IsSimulcast(encoder_config)) {
375 // Resolution bitrate limits usage is restricted to singlecast.
376 return;
377 }
378
379 // Get bitrate limits for active stream.
380 absl::optional<uint32_t> pixels =
381 VideoStreamAdapter::GetSingleActiveLayerPixels(*codec);
382 if (!pixels.has_value()) {
383 return;
384 }
385 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> bitrate_limits =
386 encoder_info.GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(*pixels);
387 if (!bitrate_limits.has_value()) {
388 return;
389 }
390
391 // Index for the active stream.
392 absl::optional<size_t> index;
393 for (size_t i = 0; i < encoder_config.simulcast_layers.size(); ++i) {
394 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[i].active)
395 index = i;
396 }
397 if (!index.has_value()) {
398 return;
399 }
400
401 int min_bitrate_bps;
402 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[*index].min_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
403 min_bitrate_bps = bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps;
404 } else {
405 min_bitrate_bps =
406 std::max(bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps,
407 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[*index].min_bitrate_bps);
408 }
409 int max_bitrate_bps;
410 if (encoder_config.simulcast_layers[*index].max_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
411 max_bitrate_bps = bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps;
412 } else {
413 max_bitrate_bps =
414 std::min(bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps,
415 encoder_config.simulcast_layers[*index].max_bitrate_bps);
416 }
417 if (min_bitrate_bps >= max_bitrate_bps) {
418 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Bitrate limits not used, min_bitrate_bps "
419 << min_bitrate_bps << " >= max_bitrate_bps "
420 << max_bitrate_bps;
421 return;
422 }
423
424 for (int i = 0; i < codec->VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers; ++i) {
425 if (codec->spatialLayers[i].active) {
426 codec->spatialLayers[i].minBitrate = min_bitrate_bps / 1000;
427 codec->spatialLayers[i].maxBitrate = max_bitrate_bps / 1000;
428 codec->spatialLayers[i].targetBitrate =
429 std::min(codec->spatialLayers[i].targetBitrate,
430 codec->spatialLayers[i].maxBitrate);
431 break;
432 }
433 }
434}

436void ApplyEncoderBitrateLimitsIfSingleActiveStream(
437 const VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo& encoder_info,
438 const std::vector<VideoStream>& encoder_config_layers,
439 std::vector<VideoStream>* streams) {
440 // Apply limits if simulcast with one active stream (expect lowest).
441 bool single_active_stream =
442 streams->size() > 1 && NumActiveStreams(*streams) == 1 &&
443 !streams->front().active && NumActiveStreams(encoder_config_layers) == 1;
444 if (!single_active_stream) {
445 return;
446 }
447
448 // Index for the active stream.
449 size_t index = 0;
450 for (size_t i = 0; i < encoder_config_layers.size(); ++i) {
451 if (encoder_config_layers[i].active)
452 index = i;
453 }
454 if (streams->size() < (index + 1) || !(*streams)[index].active) {
455 return;
456 }
457
458 // Get bitrate limits for active stream.
459 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> encoder_bitrate_limits =
460 encoder_info.GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(
461 (*streams)[index].width * (*streams)[index].height);
462 if (!encoder_bitrate_limits) {
463 return;
464 }
465
466 // If bitrate limits are set by RtpEncodingParameters, use intersection.
467 int min_bitrate_bps;
468 if (encoder_config_layers[index].min_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
469 min_bitrate_bps = encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps;
470 } else {
471 min_bitrate_bps = std::max(encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps,
472 (*streams)[index].min_bitrate_bps);
473 }
474 int max_bitrate_bps;
475 if (encoder_config_layers[index].max_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
476 max_bitrate_bps = encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps;
477 } else {
478 max_bitrate_bps = std::min(encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps,
479 (*streams)[index].max_bitrate_bps);
480 }
481 if (min_bitrate_bps >= max_bitrate_bps) {
482 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder bitrate limits"
483 << " (min=" << encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps
484 << ", max=" << encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps
485 << ") do not intersect with stream limits"
486 << " (min=" << (*streams)[index].min_bitrate_bps
487 << ", max=" << (*streams)[index].max_bitrate_bps
488 << "). Encoder bitrate limits not used.";
489 return;
490 }
491
492 (*streams)[index].min_bitrate_bps = min_bitrate_bps;
493 (*streams)[index].max_bitrate_bps = max_bitrate_bps;
494 (*streams)[index].target_bitrate_bps =
495 std::min((*streams)[index].target_bitrate_bps,
496 encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps);
497}

502 : rate_control(),
503 encoder_target(DataRate::Zero()),
504 stable_encoder_target(DataRate::Zero()) {}

506VideoStreamEncoder::EncoderRateSettings::EncoderRateSettings(
507 const VideoBitrateAllocation& bitrate,
508 double framerate_fps,
509 DataRate bandwidth_allocation,
510 DataRate encoder_target,
511 DataRate stable_encoder_target)
512 : rate_control(bitrate, framerate_fps, bandwidth_allocation),
513 encoder_target(encoder_target),
514 stable_encoder_target(stable_encoder_target) {}
515
516bool VideoStreamEncoder::EncoderRateSettings::operator==(
517 const EncoderRateSettings& rhs) const {
518 return rate_control == rhs.rate_control &&
519 encoder_target == rhs.encoder_target &&
520 stable_encoder_target == rhs.stable_encoder_target;
521}
522
523bool VideoStreamEncoder::EncoderRateSettings::operator!=(
524 const EncoderRateSettings& rhs) const {
525 return !(*this == rhs);
526}

528class VideoStreamEncoder::DegradationPreferenceManager
529 : public DegradationPreferenceProvider {
530 public:
531 explicit DegradationPreferenceManager(
532 VideoStreamAdapter* video_stream_adapter)
533 : degradation_preference_(DegradationPreference::DISABLED),
534 is_screenshare_(false),
535 effective_degradation_preference_(DegradationPreference::DISABLED),
536 video_stream_adapter_(video_stream_adapter) {
537 RTC_DCHECK(video_stream_adapter_);
538 sequence_checker_.Detach();
539 }
540
541 ~DegradationPreferenceManager() override = default;
542
543 DegradationPreference degradation_preference() const override {
544 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
545 return effective_degradation_preference_;
546 }
547
548 void SetDegradationPreference(DegradationPreference degradation_preference) {
549 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
550 degradation_preference_ = degradation_preference;
551 MaybeUpdateEffectiveDegradationPreference();
552 }
553
554 void SetIsScreenshare(bool is_screenshare) {
555 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
556 is_screenshare_ = is_screenshare;
557 MaybeUpdateEffectiveDegradationPreference();
558 }
559
560 private:
561 void MaybeUpdateEffectiveDegradationPreference()
562 RTC_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_) {
563 DegradationPreference effective_degradation_preference =
564 (is_screenshare_ &&
565 degradation_preference_ == DegradationPreference::BALANCED)
566 ? DegradationPreference::MAINTAIN_RESOLUTION
567 : degradation_preference_;
568
569 if (effective_degradation_preference != effective_degradation_preference_) {
570 effective_degradation_preference_ = effective_degradation_preference;
571 video_stream_adapter_->SetDegradationPreference(
572 effective_degradation_preference);
573 }
574 }
575
576 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker sequence_checker_;
577 DegradationPreference degradation_preference_
578 RTC_GUARDED_BY(&sequence_checker_);
579 bool is_screenshare_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&sequence_checker_);
580 DegradationPreference effective_degradation_preference_
581 RTC_GUARDED_BY(&sequence_checker_);
582 VideoStreamAdapter* video_stream_adapter_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(&sequence_checker_);
583};

585VideoStreamEncoder::VideoStreamEncoder(
586 Clock* clock,
587 uint32_t number_of_cores,
588 VideoStreamEncoderObserver* encoder_stats_observer,
589 const VideoStreamEncoderSettings& settings,
590 std::unique_ptr<OveruseFrameDetector> overuse_detector,
591 TaskQueueFactory* task_queue_factory,
592 BitrateAllocationCallbackType allocation_cb_type)
593 : main_queue_(TaskQueueBase::Current()),
594 number_of_cores_(number_of_cores),
595 sink_(nullptr),
596 settings_(settings),
597 allocation_cb_type_(allocation_cb_type),
598 rate_control_settings_(RateControlSettings::ParseFromFieldTrials()),
599 encoder_selector_(settings.encoder_factory->GetEncoderSelector()),
600 encoder_stats_observer_(encoder_stats_observer),
601 encoder_initialized_(false),
602 max_framerate_(-1),
603 pending_encoder_reconfiguration_(false),
604 pending_encoder_creation_(false),
605 crop_width_(0),
606 crop_height_(0),
607 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_(absl::nullopt),
608 max_data_payload_length_(0),
609 encoder_paused_and_dropped_frame_(false),
610 was_encode_called_since_last_initialization_(false),
611 encoder_failed_(false),
612 clock_(clock),
613 posted_frames_waiting_for_encode_(0),
614 last_captured_timestamp_(0),
615 delta_ntp_internal_ms_(clock_->CurrentNtpInMilliseconds() -
616 clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
617 last_frame_log_ms_(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()),
618 captured_frame_count_(0),
619 dropped_frame_cwnd_pushback_count_(0),
620 dropped_frame_encoder_block_count_(0),
621 pending_frame_post_time_us_(0),
622 accumulated_update_rect_{0, 0, 0, 0},
623 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_(true),
624 animation_start_time_(Timestamp::PlusInfinity()),
625 cap_resolution_due_to_video_content_(false),
626 expect_resize_state_(ExpectResizeState::kNoResize),
627 fec_controller_override_(nullptr),
628 force_disable_frame_dropper_(false),
629 input_framerate_(kFrameRateAvergingWindowSizeMs, 1000),
630 pending_frame_drops_(0),
631 cwnd_frame_counter_(0),
632 next_frame_types_(1, VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta),
633 frame_encode_metadata_writer_(this),
634 experiment_groups_(GetExperimentGroups()),
635 automatic_animation_detection_experiment_(
636 ParseAutomatincAnimationDetectionFieldTrial()),
637 input_state_provider_(encoder_stats_observer),
638 video_stream_adapter_(
639 std::make_unique<VideoStreamAdapter>(&input_state_provider_,
640 encoder_stats_observer)),
641 resource_adaptation_processor_(
642 std::make_unique<ResourceAdaptationProcessor>(
643 video_stream_adapter_.get())),
644 degradation_preference_manager_(
645 std::make_unique<DegradationPreferenceManager>(
646 video_stream_adapter_.get())),
647 adaptation_constraints_(),
648 stream_resource_manager_(&input_state_provider_,
649 encoder_stats_observer,
650 clock_,
651 settings_.experiment_cpu_load_estimator,
652 std::move(overuse_detector),
653 degradation_preference_manager_.get()),
654 video_source_sink_controller_(/*sink=*/this,
655 /*source=*/nullptr),
656 default_limits_allowed_(
657 !field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-DefaultBitrateLimitsKillSwitch")),
658 qp_parsing_allowed_(
659 !field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-QpParsingKillSwitch")),
660 encoder_queue_(task_queue_factory->CreateTaskQueue(
661 "EncoderQueue",
662 TaskQueueFactory::Priority::NORMAL)) {
663 RTC_DCHECK(main_queue_);
664 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_stats_observer);
665 RTC_DCHECK_GE(number_of_cores, 1);
666
667 stream_resource_manager_.Initialize(&encoder_queue_);
668
669 rtc::Event initialize_processor_event;
670 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, &initialize_processor_event] {
671 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
672 resource_adaptation_processor_->SetTaskQueue(encoder_queue_.Get());
673 stream_resource_manager_.SetAdaptationProcessor(
674 resource_adaptation_processor_.get(), video_stream_adapter_.get());
675 resource_adaptation_processor_->AddResourceLimitationsListener(
676 &stream_resource_manager_);
677 video_stream_adapter_->AddRestrictionsListener(&stream_resource_manager_);
678 video_stream_adapter_->AddRestrictionsListener(this);
679 stream_resource_manager_.MaybeInitializePixelLimitResource();
680
681 // Add the stream resource manager's resources to the processor.
682 adaptation_constraints_ = stream_resource_manager_.AdaptationConstraints();
683 for (auto* constraint : adaptation_constraints_) {
684 video_stream_adapter_->AddAdaptationConstraint(constraint);
685 }
686 initialize_processor_event.Set();
687 });
688 initialize_processor_event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
689}

691VideoStreamEncoder::~VideoStreamEncoder() {
692 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_queue_);
693 RTC_DCHECK(!video_source_sink_controller_.HasSource())
694 << "Must call ::Stop() before destruction.";
695}
696
697void VideoStreamEncoder::Stop() {
698 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_queue_);
699 video_source_sink_controller_.SetSource(nullptr);
700
701 rtc::Event shutdown_event;
702
703 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, &shutdown_event] {
704 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
705 if (resource_adaptation_processor_) {
706 stream_resource_manager_.StopManagedResources();
707 for (auto* constraint : adaptation_constraints_) {
708 video_stream_adapter_->RemoveAdaptationConstraint(constraint);
709 }
710 for (auto& resource : additional_resources_) {
711 stream_resource_manager_.RemoveResource(resource);
712 }
713 additional_resources_.clear();
714 video_stream_adapter_->RemoveRestrictionsListener(this);
715 video_stream_adapter_->RemoveRestrictionsListener(
716 &stream_resource_manager_);
717 resource_adaptation_processor_->RemoveResourceLimitationsListener(
718 &stream_resource_manager_);
719 stream_resource_manager_.SetAdaptationProcessor(nullptr, nullptr);
720 resource_adaptation_processor_.reset();
721 }
722 rate_allocator_ = nullptr;
723 ReleaseEncoder();
724 encoder_ = nullptr;
725 shutdown_event.Set();
726 });
727 shutdown_event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);
728}

755 map_resource_event.Wait(rtc::Event::kForever);

806
807void VideoStreamEncoder::ConfigureEncoder(VideoEncoderConfig config,
808 size_t max_data_payload_length) {
809 encoder_queue_.PostTask(
810 [this, config = std::move(config), max_data_payload_length]() mutable {
811 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
812 RTC_DCHECK(sink_);
813 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "ConfigureEncoder requested.";
814
815 pending_encoder_creation_ =
816 (!encoder_ || encoder_config_.video_format != config.video_format ||
817 max_data_payload_length_ != max_data_payload_length);
818 encoder_config_ = std::move(config);
819 max_data_payload_length_ = max_data_payload_length;
820 pending_encoder_reconfiguration_ = true;
821
822 // Reconfigure the encoder now if the encoder has an internal source or
823 // if the frame resolution is known. Otherwise, the reconfiguration is
824 // deferred until the next frame to minimize the number of
825 // reconfigurations. The codec configuration depends on incoming video
826 // frame size.
827 if (last_frame_info_) {
828 ReconfigureEncoder();
829 } else {
830 codec_info_ = settings_.encoder_factory->QueryVideoEncoder(
831 encoder_config_.video_format);
832 if (HasInternalSource()) {
833 last_frame_info_ = VideoFrameInfo(kDefaultInputPixelsWidth,
834 kDefaultInputPixelsHeight, false);
835 ReconfigureEncoder();
836 }
837 }
838 });
839}
840
841// TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/8807): Currently this always does a hard
842// reconfiguration, but this isn't always necessary. Add in logic to only update
843// the VideoBitrateAllocator and call OnEncoderConfigurationChanged with a
844// "soft" reconfiguration.
845void VideoStreamEncoder::ReconfigureEncoder() {
846 // Running on the encoder queue.
847 RTC_DCHECK(pending_encoder_reconfiguration_);
848
849 bool encoder_reset_required = false;
850 if (pending_encoder_creation_) {
851 // Destroy existing encoder instance before creating a new one. Otherwise
852 // attempt to create another instance will fail if encoder factory
853 // supports only single instance of encoder of given type.
854 encoder_.reset();
855
856 encoder_ = settings_.encoder_factory->CreateVideoEncoder(
857 encoder_config_.video_format);
858 // TODO(nisse): What to do if creating the encoder fails? Crash,
859 // or just discard incoming frames?
860 RTC_CHECK(encoder_);
861
862 if (encoder_selector_) {
863 encoder_selector_->OnCurrentEncoder(encoder_config_.video_format);
864 }
865
866 encoder_->SetFecControllerOverride(fec_controller_override_);
867
868 codec_info_ = settings_.encoder_factory->QueryVideoEncoder(
869 encoder_config_.video_format);
870
871 encoder_reset_required = true;
872 }
873
874 // Possibly adjusts scale_resolution_down_by in |encoder_config_| to limit the
875 // alignment value.
876 AlignmentAdjuster::GetAlignmentAndMaybeAdjustScaleFactors(
877 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), &encoder_config_, absl::nullopt);
878
879 std::vector<VideoStream> streams =
880 encoder_config_.video_stream_factory->CreateEncoderStreams(
881 last_frame_info_->width, last_frame_info_->height, encoder_config_);
882
883 // Get alignment when actual number of layers are known.
884 int alignment = AlignmentAdjuster::GetAlignmentAndMaybeAdjustScaleFactors(
885 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), &encoder_config_, streams.size());
886
887 // Check that the higher layers do not try to set number of temporal layers
888 // to less than 1.
889 // TODO(brandtr): Get rid of the wrapping optional as it serves no purpose
890 // at this layer.
891#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
892 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
893 RTC_DCHECK_GE(stream.num_temporal_layers.value_or(1), 1);
894 }
895#endif
896
897 // TODO(ilnik): If configured resolution is significantly less than provided,
898 // e.g. because there are not enough SSRCs for all simulcast streams,
899 // signal new resolutions via SinkWants to video source.
900
901 // Stream dimensions may be not equal to given because of a simulcast
902 // restrictions.
903 auto highest_stream = absl::c_max_element(
904 streams, [](const webrtc::VideoStream& a, const webrtc::VideoStream& b) {
905 return std::tie(a.width, a.height) < std::tie(b.width, b.height);
906 });
907 int highest_stream_width = static_cast<int>(highest_stream->width);
908 int highest_stream_height = static_cast<int>(highest_stream->height);
909 // Dimension may be reduced to be, e.g. divisible by 4.
910 RTC_CHECK_GE(last_frame_info_->width, highest_stream_width);
911 RTC_CHECK_GE(last_frame_info_->height, highest_stream_height);
912 crop_width_ = last_frame_info_->width - highest_stream_width;
913 crop_height_ = last_frame_info_->height - highest_stream_height;
914
915 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> encoder_bitrate_limits =
916 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo().GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(
917 last_frame_info_->width * last_frame_info_->height);
918
919 if (encoder_bitrate_limits) {
920 if (streams.size() == 1 && encoder_config_.simulcast_layers.size() == 1) {
921 // Bitrate limits can be set by app (in SDP or RtpEncodingParameters)
922 // or/and can be provided by encoder. In presence of both set of limits,
923 // the final set is derived as their intersection.
924 int min_bitrate_bps;
925 if (encoder_config_.simulcast_layers.empty() ||
926 encoder_config_.simulcast_layers[0].min_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
927 min_bitrate_bps = encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps;
928 } else {
929 min_bitrate_bps = std::max(encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps,
930 streams.back().min_bitrate_bps);
931 }
932
933 int max_bitrate_bps;
934 // We don't check encoder_config_.simulcast_layers[0].max_bitrate_bps
935 // here since encoder_config_.max_bitrate_bps is derived from it (as
936 // well as from other inputs).
937 if (encoder_config_.max_bitrate_bps <= 0) {
938 max_bitrate_bps = encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps;
939 } else {
940 max_bitrate_bps = std::min(encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps,
941 streams.back().max_bitrate_bps);
942 }
943
944 if (min_bitrate_bps < max_bitrate_bps) {
945 streams.back().min_bitrate_bps = min_bitrate_bps;
946 streams.back().max_bitrate_bps = max_bitrate_bps;
947 streams.back().target_bitrate_bps =
948 std::min(streams.back().target_bitrate_bps,
949 encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps);
950 } else {
951 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
952 << "Bitrate limits provided by encoder"
953 << " (min=" << encoder_bitrate_limits->min_bitrate_bps
954 << ", max=" << encoder_bitrate_limits->max_bitrate_bps
955 << ") do not intersect with limits set by app"
956 << " (min=" << streams.back().min_bitrate_bps
957 << ", max=" << encoder_config_.max_bitrate_bps
958 << "). The app bitrate limits will be used.";
959 }
960 }
961 }
962
963 ApplyEncoderBitrateLimitsIfSingleActiveStream(
964 GetEncoderInfoWithBitrateLimitUpdate(
965 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), encoder_config_, default_limits_allowed_),
966 encoder_config_.simulcast_layers, &streams);
967
968 VideoCodec codec;
969 if (!VideoCodecInitializer::SetupCodec(encoder_config_, streams, &codec)) {
970 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to create encoder configuration.";
971 }
972
973 if (encoder_config_.codec_type == kVideoCodecVP9) {
974 // Spatial layers configuration might impose some parity restrictions,
975 // thus some cropping might be needed.
976 crop_width_ = last_frame_info_->width - codec.width;
977 crop_height_ = last_frame_info_->height - codec.height;
978 ApplyVp9BitrateLimits(GetEncoderInfoWithBitrateLimitUpdate(
979 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), encoder_config_,
980 default_limits_allowed_),
981 encoder_config_, &codec);
982 }
983
984 char log_stream_buf[4 * 1024];
985 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder log_stream(log_stream_buf);
986 log_stream << "ReconfigureEncoder:\n";
987 log_stream << "Simulcast streams:\n";
988 for (size_t i = 0; i < codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams; ++i) {
989 log_stream << i << ": " << codec.simulcastStream[i].width << "x"
990 << codec.simulcastStream[i].height
991 << " fps: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].maxFramerate
992 << " min_kbps: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].minBitrate
993 << " target_kbps: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].targetBitrate
994 << " max_kbps: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].maxBitrate
995 << " max_fps: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].maxFramerate
996 << " max_qp: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].qpMax
997 << " num_tl: " << codec.simulcastStream[i].numberOfTemporalLayers
998 << " active: "
999 << (codec.simulcastStream[i].active ? "true" : "false") << "\n";
1000 }
1001 if (encoder_config_.codec_type == kVideoCodecVP9) {
1002 size_t num_spatial_layers = codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers;
1003 log_stream << "Spatial layers:\n";
1004 for (size_t i = 0; i < num_spatial_layers; ++i) {
1005 log_stream << i << ": " << codec.spatialLayers[i].width << "x"
1006 << codec.spatialLayers[i].height
1007 << " fps: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].maxFramerate
1008 << " min_kbps: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].minBitrate
1009 << " target_kbps: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].targetBitrate
1010 << " max_kbps: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].maxBitrate
1011 << " max_qp: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].qpMax
1012 << " num_tl: " << codec.spatialLayers[i].numberOfTemporalLayers
1013 << " active: "
1014 << (codec.spatialLayers[i].active ? "true" : "false") << "\n";
1015 }
1016 }
1017 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << log_stream.str();
1018
1019 codec.startBitrate = std::max(encoder_target_bitrate_bps_.value_or(0) / 1000,
1020 codec.minBitrate);
1021 codec.startBitrate = std::min(codec.startBitrate, codec.maxBitrate);
1022 codec.expect_encode_from_texture = last_frame_info_->is_texture;
1023 // Make sure the start bit rate is sane...
1024 RTC_DCHECK_LE(codec.startBitrate, 1000000);
1025 max_framerate_ = codec.maxFramerate;
1026
1027 // Inform source about max configured framerate.
1028 int max_framerate = 0;
1029 for (const auto& stream : streams) {
1030 max_framerate = std::max(stream.max_framerate, max_framerate);
1031 }
1032
1033 // The resolutions that we're actually encoding with.
1034 std::vector<rtc::VideoSinkWants::FrameSize> encoder_resolutions;
1035 // TODO(hbos): For the case of SVC, also make use of |codec.spatialLayers|.
1036 // For now, SVC layers are handled by the VP9 encoder.
1037 for (const auto& simulcastStream : codec.simulcastStream) {
1038 if (!simulcastStream.active)
1039 continue;
1040 encoder_resolutions.emplace_back(simulcastStream.width,
1041 simulcastStream.height);
1042 }
1043 main_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
1044 task_safety_, [this, max_framerate, alignment,
1045 encoder_resolutions = std::move(encoder_resolutions)]() {
1046 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_queue_);
1047 if (max_framerate !=
1048 video_source_sink_controller_.frame_rate_upper_limit() ||
1049 alignment != video_source_sink_controller_.resolution_alignment() ||
1050 encoder_resolutions !=
1051 video_source_sink_controller_.resolutions()) {
1052 video_source_sink_controller_.SetFrameRateUpperLimit(max_framerate);
1053 video_source_sink_controller_.SetResolutionAlignment(alignment);
1054 video_source_sink_controller_.SetResolutions(
1055 std::move(encoder_resolutions));
1056 video_source_sink_controller_.PushSourceSinkSettings();
1057 }
1058 }));
1059
1060 if (codec.maxBitrate == 0) {
1061 // max is one bit per pixel
1062 codec.maxBitrate =
1063 (static_cast<int>(codec.height) * static_cast<int>(codec.width) *
1064 static_cast<int>(codec.maxFramerate)) /
1065 1000;
1066 if (codec.startBitrate > codec.maxBitrate) {
1067 // But if the user tries to set a higher start bit rate we will
1068 // increase the max accordingly.
1069 codec.maxBitrate = codec.startBitrate;
1070 }
1071 }
1072
1073 if (codec.startBitrate > codec.maxBitrate) {
1074 codec.startBitrate = codec.maxBitrate;
1075 }
1076
1077 rate_allocator_ =
1078 settings_.bitrate_allocator_factory->CreateVideoBitrateAllocator(codec);
1079 rate_allocator_->SetLegacyConferenceMode(
1080 encoder_config_.legacy_conference_mode);
1081
1082 // Reset (release existing encoder) if one exists and anything except
1083 // start bitrate or max framerate has changed.
1084 if (!encoder_reset_required) {
1085 encoder_reset_required = RequiresEncoderReset(
1086 send_codec_, codec, was_encode_called_since_last_initialization_);
1087 }
1088 send_codec_ = codec;
1089
1090 // Keep the same encoder, as long as the video_format is unchanged.
1091 // Encoder creation block is split in two since EncoderInfo needed to start
1092 // CPU adaptation with the correct settings should be polled after
1093 // encoder_->InitEncode().
1094 bool success = true;
1095 if (encoder_reset_required) {
1096 ReleaseEncoder();
1097 const size_t max_data_payload_length = max_data_payload_length_ > 0
1098 ? max_data_payload_length_
1099 : kDefaultPayloadSize;
1100 if (encoder_->InitEncode(
1101 &send_codec_,
1102 VideoEncoder::Settings(settings_.capabilities, number_of_cores_,
1103 max_data_payload_length)) != 0) {
1104 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to initialize the encoder associated with "
1105 "codec type: "
1106 << CodecTypeToPayloadString(send_codec_.codecType)
1107 << " (" << send_codec_.codecType << ")";
1108 ReleaseEncoder();
1109 success = false;
1110 } else {
1111 encoder_initialized_ = true;
1112 encoder_->RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(this);
1113 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.OnEncoderInit(send_codec_,
1114 HasInternalSource());
1115 next_frame_types_.clear();
1116 next_frame_types_.resize(
1117 std::max(static_cast<int>(codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams), 1),
1118 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
1119 }
1120
1121 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.Reset();
1122 last_encode_info_ms_ = absl::nullopt;
1123 was_encode_called_since_last_initialization_ = false;
1124 }
1125
1126 // Inform dependents of updated encoder settings.
1127 OnEncoderSettingsChanged();
1128
1129 if (success) {
1130 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << " max bitrate " << codec.maxBitrate
1131 << " start bitrate " << codec.startBitrate
1132 << " max frame rate " << codec.maxFramerate
1133 << " max payload size " << max_data_payload_length_;
1134 } else {
1135 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to configure encoder.";
1136 rate_allocator_ = nullptr;
1137 }
1138
1139 if (pending_encoder_creation_) {
1140 stream_resource_manager_.ConfigureEncodeUsageResource();
1141 pending_encoder_creation_ = false;
1142 }
1143
1144 int num_layers;
1145 if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
1146 num_layers = codec.VP8()->numberOfTemporalLayers;
1147 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
1148 num_layers = codec.VP9()->numberOfTemporalLayers;
1149 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecH264) {
1150 num_layers = codec.H264()->numberOfTemporalLayers;
1151 } else if (codec.codecType == kVideoCodecGeneric &&
1152 codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams > 0) {
1153 // This is mainly for unit testing, disabling frame dropping.
1154 // TODO(sprang): Add a better way to disable frame dropping.
1155 num_layers = codec.simulcastStream[0].numberOfTemporalLayers;
1156 } else {
1157 num_layers = 1;
1158 }
1159
1160 frame_dropper_.Reset();
1161 frame_dropper_.SetRates(codec.startBitrate, max_framerate_);
1162 // Force-disable frame dropper if either:
1163 // * We have screensharing with layers.
1164 // * "WebRTC-FrameDropper" field trial is "Disabled".
1165 force_disable_frame_dropper_ =
1166 field_trial::IsDisabled(kFrameDropperFieldTrial) ||
1167 (num_layers > 1 && codec.mode == VideoCodecMode::kScreensharing);
1168
1169 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo info = encoder_->GetEncoderInfo();
1170 if (rate_control_settings_.UseEncoderBitrateAdjuster()) {
1171 bitrate_adjuster_ = std::make_unique<EncoderBitrateAdjuster>(codec);
1172 bitrate_adjuster_->OnEncoderInfo(info);
1173 }
1174
1175 if (rate_allocator_ && last_encoder_rate_settings_) {
1176 // We have a new rate allocator instance and already configured target
1177 // bitrate. Update the rate allocation and notify observers.
1178 // We must invalidate the last_encoder_rate_settings_ to ensure
1179 // the changes get propagated to all listeners.
1180 EncoderRateSettings rate_settings = *last_encoder_rate_settings_;
1181 last_encoder_rate_settings_.reset();
1182 rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps = GetInputFramerateFps();
1183
1184 SetEncoderRates(UpdateBitrateAllocation(rate_settings));
1185 }
1186
1187 encoder_stats_observer_->OnEncoderReconfigured(encoder_config_, streams);
1188
1189 pending_encoder_reconfiguration_ = false;
1190
1191 bool is_svc = false;
1192 // Set min_bitrate_bps, max_bitrate_bps, and max padding bit rate for VP9
1193 // and leave only one stream containing all necessary information.
1194 if (encoder_config_.codec_type == kVideoCodecVP9) {
1195 // Lower max bitrate to the level codec actually can produce.
1196 streams[0].max_bitrate_bps =
1197 std::min(streams[0].max_bitrate_bps,
1198 SvcRateAllocator::GetMaxBitrate(codec).bps<int>());
1199 streams[0].min_bitrate_bps = codec.spatialLayers[0].minBitrate * 1000;
1200 // target_bitrate_bps specifies the maximum padding bitrate.
1201 streams[0].target_bitrate_bps =
1202 SvcRateAllocator::GetPaddingBitrate(codec).bps<int>();
1203 streams[0].width = streams.back().width;
1204 streams[0].height = streams.back().height;
1205 is_svc = codec.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers > 1;
1206 streams.resize(1);
1207 }
1208
1209 sink_->OnEncoderConfigurationChanged(
1210 std::move(streams), is_svc, encoder_config_.content_type,
1211 encoder_config_.min_transmit_bitrate_bps);
1212
1213 stream_resource_manager_.ConfigureQualityScaler(info);
1214}
1215
1216void VideoStreamEncoder::OnEncoderSettingsChanged() {
1217 EncoderSettings encoder_settings(
1218 GetEncoderInfoWithBitrateLimitUpdate(
1219 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), encoder_config_, default_limits_allowed_),
1220 encoder_config_.Copy(), send_codec_);
1221 stream_resource_manager_.SetEncoderSettings(encoder_settings);
1222 input_state_provider_.OnEncoderSettingsChanged(encoder_settings);
1223 bool is_screenshare = encoder_settings.encoder_config().content_type ==
1224 VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen;
1225 degradation_preference_manager_->SetIsScreenshare(is_screenshare);
1226}
1227
1228void VideoStreamEncoder::OnFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame) {
1229 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&incoming_frame_race_checker_);
1230 VideoFrame incoming_frame = video_frame;
1231
1232 // Local time in webrtc time base.
1233 Timestamp now = clock_->CurrentTime();
1234
1235 // In some cases, e.g., when the frame from decoder is fed to encoder,
1236 // the timestamp may be set to the future. As the encoding pipeline assumes
1237 // capture time to be less than present time, we should reset the capture
1238 // timestamps here. Otherwise there may be issues with RTP send stream.
1239 if (incoming_frame.timestamp_us() > now.us())
1240 incoming_frame.set_timestamp_us(now.us());
1241
1242 // Capture time may come from clock with an offset and drift from clock_.
1243 int64_t capture_ntp_time_ms;
1244 if (video_frame.ntp_time_ms() > 0) {
1245 capture_ntp_time_ms = video_frame.ntp_time_ms();
1246 } else if (video_frame.render_time_ms() != 0) {
1247 capture_ntp_time_ms = video_frame.render_time_ms() + delta_ntp_internal_ms_;
1248 } else {
1249 capture_ntp_time_ms = now.ms() + delta_ntp_internal_ms_;
1250 }
1251 incoming_frame.set_ntp_time_ms(capture_ntp_time_ms);
1252
1253 // Convert NTP time, in ms, to RTP timestamp.
1254 const int kMsToRtpTimestamp = 90;
1255 incoming_frame.set_timestamp(
1256 kMsToRtpTimestamp * static_cast<uint32_t>(incoming_frame.ntp_time_ms()));
1257
1258 if (incoming_frame.ntp_time_ms() <= last_captured_timestamp_) {
1259 // We don't allow the same capture time for two frames, drop this one.
1260 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Same/old NTP timestamp ("
1261 << incoming_frame.ntp_time_ms()
1262 << " <= " << last_captured_timestamp_
1263 << ") for incoming frame. Dropping.";
1264 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, incoming_frame]() {
1265 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1266 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(incoming_frame.update_rect());
1267 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= incoming_frame.has_update_rect();
1268 });
1269 return;
1270 }
1271
1272 bool log_stats = false;
1273 if (now.ms() - last_frame_log_ms_ > kFrameLogIntervalMs) {
1274 last_frame_log_ms_ = now.ms();
1275 log_stats = true;
1276 }
1277
1278 last_captured_timestamp_ = incoming_frame.ntp_time_ms();
1279
1280 int64_t post_time_us = clock_->CurrentTime().us();
1281 ++posted_frames_waiting_for_encode_;
1282
1283 encoder_queue_.PostTask(
1284 [this, incoming_frame, post_time_us, log_stats]() {
1285 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1286 encoder_stats_observer_->OnIncomingFrame(incoming_frame.width(),
1287 incoming_frame.height());
1288 ++captured_frame_count_;
1289 const int posted_frames_waiting_for_encode =
1290 posted_frames_waiting_for_encode_.fetch_sub(1);
1291 RTC_DCHECK_GT(posted_frames_waiting_for_encode, 0);
1292 CheckForAnimatedContent(incoming_frame, post_time_us);
1293 bool cwnd_frame_drop =
1294 cwnd_frame_drop_interval_ &&
1295 (cwnd_frame_counter_++ % cwnd_frame_drop_interval_.value() == 0);
1296 if (posted_frames_waiting_for_encode == 1 && !cwnd_frame_drop) {
1297 MaybeEncodeVideoFrame(incoming_frame, post_time_us);
1298 } else {
1299 if (cwnd_frame_drop) {
1300 // Frame drop by congestion window pushback. Do not encode this
1301 // frame.
1302 ++dropped_frame_cwnd_pushback_count_;
1303 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1304 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kCongestionWindow);
1305 } else {
1306 // There is a newer frame in flight. Do not encode this frame.
1307 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1308 << "Incoming frame dropped due to that the encoder is blocked.";
1309 ++dropped_frame_encoder_block_count_;
1310 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1311 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kEncoderQueue);
1312 }
1313 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(incoming_frame.update_rect());
1314 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= incoming_frame.has_update_rect();
1315 }
1316 if (log_stats) {
1317 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Number of frames: captured "
1318 << captured_frame_count_
1319 << ", dropped (due to congestion window pushback) "
1320 << dropped_frame_cwnd_pushback_count_
1321 << ", dropped (due to encoder blocked) "
1322 << dropped_frame_encoder_block_count_
1323 << ", interval_ms " << kFrameLogIntervalMs;
1324 captured_frame_count_ = 0;
1325 dropped_frame_cwnd_pushback_count_ = 0;
1326 dropped_frame_encoder_block_count_ = 0;
1327 }
1328 });
1329}
1330
1331void VideoStreamEncoder::OnDiscardedFrame() {
1332 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1333 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kSource);
1334}
1335
1336bool VideoStreamEncoder::EncoderPaused() const {
1337 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1338 // Pause video if paused by caller or as long as the network is down or the
1339 // pacer queue has grown too large in buffered mode.
1340 // If the pacer queue has grown too large or the network is down,
1341 // |last_encoder_rate_settings_->encoder_target| will be 0.
1342 return !last_encoder_rate_settings_ ||
1343 last_encoder_rate_settings_->encoder_target == DataRate::Zero();
1344}
1345
1346void VideoStreamEncoder::TraceFrameDropStart() {
1347 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1348 // Start trace event only on the first frame after encoder is paused.
1349 if (!encoder_paused_and_dropped_frame_) {
1350 TRACE_EVENT_ASYNC_BEGIN0("webrtc", "EncoderPaused", this);
1351 }
1352 encoder_paused_and_dropped_frame_ = true;
1353}
1354
1355void VideoStreamEncoder::TraceFrameDropEnd() {
1356 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1357 // End trace event on first frame after encoder resumes, if frame was dropped.
1358 if (encoder_paused_and_dropped_frame_) {
1359 TRACE_EVENT_ASYNC_END0("webrtc", "EncoderPaused", this);
1360 }
1361 encoder_paused_and_dropped_frame_ = false;
1362}
1363
1364VideoStreamEncoder::EncoderRateSettings
1365VideoStreamEncoder::UpdateBitrateAllocation(
1366 const EncoderRateSettings& rate_settings) {
1367 VideoBitrateAllocation new_allocation;
1368 // Only call allocators if bitrate > 0 (ie, not suspended), otherwise they
1369 // might cap the bitrate to the min bitrate configured.
1370 if (rate_allocator_ && rate_settings.encoder_target > DataRate::Zero()) {
1371 new_allocation = rate_allocator_->Allocate(VideoBitrateAllocationParameters(
1372 rate_settings.encoder_target, rate_settings.stable_encoder_target,
1373 rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps));
1374 }
1375
1376 EncoderRateSettings new_rate_settings = rate_settings;
1377 new_rate_settings.rate_control.target_bitrate = new_allocation;
1378 new_rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate = new_allocation;
1379 // VideoBitrateAllocator subclasses may allocate a bitrate higher than the
1380 // target in order to sustain the min bitrate of the video codec. In this
1381 // case, make sure the bandwidth allocation is at least equal the allocation
1382 // as that is part of the document contract for that field.
1383 new_rate_settings.rate_control.bandwidth_allocation =
1384 std::max(new_rate_settings.rate_control.bandwidth_allocation,
1385 DataRate::BitsPerSec(
1386 new_rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate.get_sum_bps()));
1387
1388 if (bitrate_adjuster_) {
1389 VideoBitrateAllocation adjusted_allocation =
1390 bitrate_adjuster_->AdjustRateAllocation(new_rate_settings.rate_control);
1391 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "Adjusting allocation, fps = "
1392 << rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps << ", from "
1393 << new_allocation.ToString() << ", to "
1394 << adjusted_allocation.ToString();
1395 new_rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate = adjusted_allocation;
1396 }
1397
1398 return new_rate_settings;
1399}
1400
1401uint32_t VideoStreamEncoder::GetInputFramerateFps() {
1402 const uint32_t default_fps = max_framerate_ != -1 ? max_framerate_ : 30;
1403 absl::optional<uint32_t> input_fps =
1404 input_framerate_.Rate(clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
1405 if (!input_fps || *input_fps == 0) {
1406 return default_fps;
1407 }
1408 return *input_fps;
1409}
1410
1411void VideoStreamEncoder::SetEncoderRates(
1412 const EncoderRateSettings& rate_settings) {
1413 RTC_DCHECK_GT(rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps, 0.0);
1414 bool rate_control_changed =
1415 (!last_encoder_rate_settings_.has_value() ||
1416 last_encoder_rate_settings_->rate_control != rate_settings.rate_control);
1417 // For layer allocation signal we care only about the target bitrate (not the
1418 // adjusted one) and the target fps.
1419 bool layer_allocation_changed =
1420 !last_encoder_rate_settings_.has_value() ||
1421 last_encoder_rate_settings_->rate_control.target_bitrate !=
1422 rate_settings.rate_control.target_bitrate ||
1423 last_encoder_rate_settings_->rate_control.framerate_fps !=
1424 rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps;
1425
1426 if (last_encoder_rate_settings_ != rate_settings) {
1427 last_encoder_rate_settings_ = rate_settings;
1428 }
1429
1430 if (!encoder_) {
1431 return;
1432 }
1433
1434 // |bitrate_allocation| is 0 it means that the network is down or the send
1435 // pacer is full. We currently only report this if the encoder has an internal
1436 // source. If the encoder does not have an internal source, higher levels
1437 // are expected to not call AddVideoFrame. We do this since it is unclear
1438 // how current encoder implementations behave when given a zero target
1439 // bitrate.
1440 // TODO(perkj): Make sure all known encoder implementations handle zero
1441 // target bitrate and remove this check.
1442 if (!HasInternalSource() &&
1443 rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate.get_sum_bps() == 0) {
1444 return;
1445 }
1446
1447 if (rate_control_changed) {
1448 encoder_->SetRates(rate_settings.rate_control);
1449
1450 encoder_stats_observer_->OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
1451 send_codec_, rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate);
1452 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.OnSetRates(
1453 rate_settings.rate_control.bitrate,
1454 static_cast<uint32_t>(rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps + 0.5));
1455 stream_resource_manager_.SetEncoderRates(rate_settings.rate_control);
1456 if (layer_allocation_changed &&
1457 allocation_cb_type_ ==
1458 BitrateAllocationCallbackType::kVideoLayersAllocation) {
1459 sink_->OnVideoLayersAllocationUpdated(CreateVideoLayersAllocation(
1460 send_codec_, rate_settings.rate_control, encoder_->GetEncoderInfo()));
1461 }
1462 }
1463 if ((allocation_cb_type_ ==
1464 BitrateAllocationCallbackType::kVideoBitrateAllocation) ||
1465 (encoder_config_.content_type ==
1466 VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen &&
1467 allocation_cb_type_ == BitrateAllocationCallbackType::
1468 kVideoBitrateAllocationWhenScreenSharing)) {
1469 sink_->OnBitrateAllocationUpdated(
1470 // Update allocation according to info from encoder. An encoder may
1471 // choose to not use all layers due to for example HW.
1472 UpdateAllocationFromEncoderInfo(
1473 rate_settings.rate_control.target_bitrate,
1474 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo()));
1475 }
1476}
1477
1478void VideoStreamEncoder::MaybeEncodeVideoFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame,
1479 int64_t time_when_posted_us) {
1480 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1481 input_state_provider_.OnFrameSizeObserved(video_frame.size());
1482
1483 if (!last_frame_info_ || video_frame.width() != last_frame_info_->width ||
1484 video_frame.height() != last_frame_info_->height ||
1485 video_frame.is_texture() != last_frame_info_->is_texture) {
1486 pending_encoder_reconfiguration_ = true;
1487 last_frame_info_ = VideoFrameInfo(video_frame.width(), video_frame.height(),
1488 video_frame.is_texture());
1489 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Video frame parameters changed: dimensions="
1490 << last_frame_info_->width << "x"
1491 << last_frame_info_->height
1492 << ", texture=" << last_frame_info_->is_texture << ".";
1493 // Force full frame update, since resolution has changed.
1494 accumulated_update_rect_ =
1495 VideoFrame::UpdateRect{0, 0, video_frame.width(), video_frame.height()};
1496 }
1497
1498 // We have to create the encoder before the frame drop logic,
1499 // because the latter depends on encoder_->GetScalingSettings.
1500 // According to the testcase
1501 // InitialFrameDropOffWhenEncoderDisabledScaling, the return value
1502 // from GetScalingSettings should enable or disable the frame drop.
1503
1504 // Update input frame rate before we start using it. If we update it after
1505 // any potential frame drop we are going to artificially increase frame sizes.
1506 // Poll the rate before updating, otherwise we risk the rate being estimated
1507 // a little too high at the start of the call when then window is small.
1508 uint32_t framerate_fps = GetInputFramerateFps();
1509 input_framerate_.Update(1u, clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
1510
1511 int64_t now_ms = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
1512 if (pending_encoder_reconfiguration_) {
1513 ReconfigureEncoder();
1514 last_parameters_update_ms_.emplace(now_ms);
1515 } else if (!last_parameters_update_ms_ ||
1516 now_ms - *last_parameters_update_ms_ >=
1517 kParameterUpdateIntervalMs) {
1518 if (last_encoder_rate_settings_) {
1519 // Clone rate settings before update, so that SetEncoderRates() will
1520 // actually detect the change between the input and
1521 // |last_encoder_rate_setings_|, triggering the call to SetRate() on the
1522 // encoder.
1523 EncoderRateSettings new_rate_settings = *last_encoder_rate_settings_;
1524 new_rate_settings.rate_control.framerate_fps =
1525 static_cast<double>(framerate_fps);
1526 SetEncoderRates(UpdateBitrateAllocation(new_rate_settings));
1527 }
1528 last_parameters_update_ms_.emplace(now_ms);
1529 }
1530
1531 // Because pending frame will be dropped in any case, we need to
1532 // remember its updated region.
1533 if (pending_frame_) {
1534 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1535 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kEncoderQueue);
1536 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(pending_frame_->update_rect());
1537 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= pending_frame_->has_update_rect();
1538 }
1539
1540 if (DropDueToSize(video_frame.size())) {
1541 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Dropping frame. Too large for target bitrate.";
1542 stream_resource_manager_.OnFrameDroppedDueToSize();
1543 // Storing references to a native buffer risks blocking frame capture.
1544 if (video_frame.video_frame_buffer()->type() !=
1545 VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNative) {
1546 pending_frame_ = video_frame;
1547 pending_frame_post_time_us_ = time_when_posted_us;
1548 } else {
1549 // Ensure that any previously stored frame is dropped.
1550 pending_frame_.reset();
1551 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(video_frame.update_rect());
1552 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= video_frame.has_update_rect();
1553 }
1554 return;
1555 }
1556 stream_resource_manager_.OnMaybeEncodeFrame();
1557
1558 if (EncoderPaused()) {
1559 // Storing references to a native buffer risks blocking frame capture.
1560 if (video_frame.video_frame_buffer()->type() !=
1561 VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNative) {
1562 if (pending_frame_)
1563 TraceFrameDropStart();
1564 pending_frame_ = video_frame;
1565 pending_frame_post_time_us_ = time_when_posted_us;
1566 } else {
1567 // Ensure that any previously stored frame is dropped.
1568 pending_frame_.reset();
1569 TraceFrameDropStart();
1570 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(video_frame.update_rect());
1571 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= video_frame.has_update_rect();
1572 }
1573 return;
1574 }
1575
1576 pending_frame_.reset();
1577
1578 frame_dropper_.Leak(framerate_fps);
1579 // Frame dropping is enabled iff frame dropping is not force-disabled, and
1580 // rate controller is not trusted.
1581 const bool frame_dropping_enabled =
1582 !force_disable_frame_dropper_ &&
1583 !encoder_info_.has_trusted_rate_controller;
1584 frame_dropper_.Enable(frame_dropping_enabled);
1585 if (frame_dropping_enabled && frame_dropper_.DropFrame()) {
1586 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1587 << "Drop Frame: "
1588 "target bitrate "
1589 << (last_encoder_rate_settings_
1590 ? last_encoder_rate_settings_->encoder_target.bps()
1591 : 0)
1592 << ", input frame rate " << framerate_fps;
1593 OnDroppedFrame(
1594 EncodedImageCallback::DropReason::kDroppedByMediaOptimizations);
1595 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(video_frame.update_rect());
1596 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ &= video_frame.has_update_rect();
1597 return;
1598 }
1599
1600 EncodeVideoFrame(video_frame, time_when_posted_us);
1601}
1602
1603void VideoStreamEncoder::EncodeVideoFrame(const VideoFrame& video_frame,
1604 int64_t time_when_posted_us) {
1605 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1606
1607 // If the encoder fail we can't continue to encode frames. When this happens
1608 // the WebrtcVideoSender is notified and the whole VideoSendStream is
1609 // recreated.
1610 if (encoder_failed_)
1611 return;
1612
1613 TraceFrameDropEnd();
1614
1615 // Encoder metadata needs to be updated before encode complete callback.
1616 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo info = encoder_->GetEncoderInfo();
1617 if (info.implementation_name != encoder_info_.implementation_name) {
1618 encoder_stats_observer_->OnEncoderImplementationChanged(
1619 info.implementation_name);
1620 if (bitrate_adjuster_) {
1621 // Encoder implementation changed, reset overshoot detector states.
1622 bitrate_adjuster_->Reset();
1623 }
1624 }
1625
1626 if (encoder_info_ != info) {
1627 OnEncoderSettingsChanged();
1628 stream_resource_manager_.ConfigureEncodeUsageResource();
1629 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Encoder settings changed from "
1630 << encoder_info_.ToString() << " to " << info.ToString();
1631 }
1632
1633 if (bitrate_adjuster_) {
1634 for (size_t si = 0; si < kMaxSpatialLayers; ++si) {
1635 if (info.fps_allocation[si] != encoder_info_.fps_allocation[si]) {
1636 bitrate_adjuster_->OnEncoderInfo(info);
1637 break;
1638 }
1639 }
1640 }
1641 encoder_info_ = info;
1642 last_encode_info_ms_ = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
1643
1644 VideoFrame out_frame(video_frame);
1645 // Crop or scale the frame if needed. Dimension may be reduced to fit encoder
1646 // requirements, e.g. some encoders may require them to be divisible by 4.
1647 if ((crop_width_ > 0 || crop_height_ > 0) &&
1648 (out_frame.video_frame_buffer()->type() !=
1649 VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNative ||
1650 !info.supports_native_handle)) {
1651 int cropped_width = video_frame.width() - crop_width_;
1652 int cropped_height = video_frame.height() - crop_height_;
1653 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> cropped_buffer;
1654 // TODO(ilnik): Remove scaling if cropping is too big, as it should never
1655 // happen after SinkWants signaled correctly from ReconfigureEncoder.
1656 VideoFrame::UpdateRect update_rect = video_frame.update_rect();
1657 if (crop_width_ < 4 && crop_height_ < 4) {
1658 // The difference is small, crop without scaling.
1659 cropped_buffer = video_frame.video_frame_buffer()->CropAndScale(
1660 crop_width_ / 2, crop_height_ / 2, cropped_width, cropped_height,
1661 cropped_width, cropped_height);
1662 update_rect.offset_x -= crop_width_ / 2;
1663 update_rect.offset_y -= crop_height_ / 2;
1664 update_rect.Intersect(
1665 VideoFrame::UpdateRect{0, 0, cropped_width, cropped_height});
1666
1667 } else {
1668 // The difference is large, scale it.
1669 cropped_buffer = video_frame.video_frame_buffer()->Scale(cropped_width,
1670 cropped_height);
1671 if (!update_rect.IsEmpty()) {
1672 // Since we can't reason about pixels after scaling, we invalidate whole
1673 // picture, if anything changed.
1674 update_rect =
1675 VideoFrame::UpdateRect{0, 0, cropped_width, cropped_height};
1676 }
1677 }
1678 if (!cropped_buffer) {
1679 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Cropping and scaling frame failed, dropping frame.";
1680 return;
1681 }
1682
1683 out_frame.set_video_frame_buffer(cropped_buffer);
1684 out_frame.set_update_rect(update_rect);
1685 out_frame.set_ntp_time_ms(video_frame.ntp_time_ms());
1686 // Since accumulated_update_rect_ is constructed before cropping,
1687 // we can't trust it. If any changes were pending, we invalidate whole
1688 // frame here.
1689 if (!accumulated_update_rect_.IsEmpty()) {
1690 accumulated_update_rect_ =
1691 VideoFrame::UpdateRect{0, 0, out_frame.width(), out_frame.height()};
1692 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ = false;
1693 }
1694 }
1695
1696 if (!accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_) {
1697 out_frame.clear_update_rect();
1698 } else if (!accumulated_update_rect_.IsEmpty() &&
1699 out_frame.has_update_rect()) {
1700 accumulated_update_rect_.Union(out_frame.update_rect());
1701 accumulated_update_rect_.Intersect(
1702 VideoFrame::UpdateRect{0, 0, out_frame.width(), out_frame.height()});
1703 out_frame.set_update_rect(accumulated_update_rect_);
1704 accumulated_update_rect_.MakeEmptyUpdate();
1705 }
1706 accumulated_update_rect_is_valid_ = true;
1707
1708 TRACE_EVENT_ASYNC_STEP0("webrtc", "Video", video_frame.render_time_ms(),
1709 "Encode");
1710
1711 stream_resource_manager_.OnEncodeStarted(out_frame, time_when_posted_us);
1712
1713 // The encoder should get the size that it expects.
1714 RTC_DCHECK(send_codec_.width <= out_frame.width() &&
1715 send_codec_.height <= out_frame.height())
1716 << "Encoder configured to " << send_codec_.width << "x"
1717 << send_codec_.height << " received a too small frame "
1718 << out_frame.width() << "x" << out_frame.height();
1719
1720 TRACE_EVENT1("webrtc", "VCMGenericEncoder::Encode", "timestamp",
1721 out_frame.timestamp());
1722
1723 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.OnEncodeStarted(out_frame);
1724
1725 const int32_t encode_status = encoder_->Encode(out_frame, &next_frame_types_);
1726 was_encode_called_since_last_initialization_ = true;
1727
1728 if (encode_status < 0) {
1729 if (encode_status == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ENCODER_FAILURE) {
1730 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Encoder failed, failing encoder format: "
1731 << encoder_config_.video_format.ToString();
1732
1733 if (settings_.encoder_switch_request_callback) {
1734 if (encoder_selector_) {
1735 if (auto encoder = encoder_selector_->OnEncoderBroken()) {
1736 QueueRequestEncoderSwitch(*encoder);
1737 }
1738 } else {
1739 encoder_failed_ = true;
1740 main_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [this]() {
1741 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_queue_);
1742 settings_.encoder_switch_request_callback->RequestEncoderFallback();
1743 }));
1744 }
1745 } else {
1746 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR)
1747 << "Encoder failed but no encoder fallback callback is registered";
1748 }
1749 } else {
1750 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to encode frame. Error code: "
1751 << encode_status;
1752 }
1753
1754 return;
1755 }
1756
1757 for (auto& it : next_frame_types_) {
1758 it = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
1759 }
1760}
1761
1762void VideoStreamEncoder::SendKeyFrame() {
1763 if (!encoder_queue_.IsCurrent()) {
1764 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this] { SendKeyFrame(); });
1765 return;
1766 }
1767 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1768 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "OnKeyFrameRequest");
1769 RTC_DCHECK(!next_frame_types_.empty());
1770
1771 // TODO(webrtc:10615): Map keyframe request to spatial layer.
1772 std::fill(next_frame_types_.begin(), next_frame_types_.end(),
1773 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
1774
1775 if (HasInternalSource()) {
1776 // Try to request the frame if we have an external encoder with
1777 // internal source since AddVideoFrame never will be called.
1778
1779 // TODO(nisse): Used only with internal source. Delete as soon as
1780 // that feature is removed. The only implementation I've been able
1781 // to find ignores what's in the frame. With one exception: It seems
1782 // a few test cases, e.g.,
1783 // VideoSendStreamTest.VideoSendStreamStopSetEncoderRateToZero, set
1784 // internal_source to true and use FakeEncoder. And the latter will
1785 // happily encode this 1x1 frame and pass it on down the pipeline.
1786 if (encoder_->Encode(VideoFrame::Builder()
1787 .set_video_frame_buffer(I420Buffer::Create(1, 1))
1788 .set_rotation(kVideoRotation_0)
1789 .set_timestamp_us(0)
1790 .build(),
1791 &next_frame_types_) == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
1792 // Try to remove just-performed keyframe request, if stream still exists.
1793 std::fill(next_frame_types_.begin(), next_frame_types_.end(),
1794 VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta);
1795 }
1796 }
1797}

1812
1813EncodedImageCallback::Result VideoStreamEncoder::OnEncodedImage(
1814 const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
1815 const CodecSpecificInfo* codec_specific_info) {
1816 TRACE_EVENT_INSTANT1("webrtc", "VCMEncodedFrameCallback::Encoded",
1817 "timestamp", encoded_image.Timestamp());
1818 const size_t spatial_idx = encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(0);
1819 EncodedImage image_copy(encoded_image);
1820
1821 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.FillTimingInfo(spatial_idx, &image_copy);
1822
1823 frame_encode_metadata_writer_.UpdateBitstream(codec_specific_info,
1824 &image_copy);
1825
1826 VideoCodecType codec_type = codec_specific_info
1827 ? codec_specific_info->codecType
1828 : VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecGeneric;
1829
1830 if (image_copy.qp_ < 0 && qp_parsing_allowed_) {
1831 // Parse encoded frame QP if that was not provided by encoder.
1832 image_copy.qp_ = qp_parser_
1833 .Parse(codec_type, spatial_idx, image_copy.data(),
1834 image_copy.size())
1835 .value_or(-1);
1836 }
1837
1838 // Piggyback ALR experiment group id and simulcast id into the content type.
1839 const uint8_t experiment_id =
1840 experiment_groups_[videocontenttypehelpers::IsScreenshare(
1841 image_copy.content_type_)];
1842
1843 // TODO(ilnik): This will force content type extension to be present even
1844 // for realtime video. At the expense of miniscule overhead we will get
1845 // sliced receive statistics.
1846 RTC_CHECK(videocontenttypehelpers::SetExperimentId(&image_copy.content_type_,
1847 experiment_id));
1848 // We count simulcast streams from 1 on the wire. That's why we set simulcast
1849 // id in content type to +1 of that is actual simulcast index. This is because
1850 // value 0 on the wire is reserved for 'no simulcast stream specified'.
1851 RTC_CHECK(videocontenttypehelpers::SetSimulcastId(
1852 &image_copy.content_type_, static_cast<uint8_t>(spatial_idx + 1)));
1853
1854 // Currently internal quality scaler is used for VP9 instead of webrtc qp
1855 // scaler (in no-svc case or if only a single spatial layer is encoded).
1856 // It has to be explicitly detected and reported to adaptation metrics.
1857 // Post a task because |send_codec_| requires |encoder_queue_| lock.
1858 unsigned int image_width = image_copy._encodedWidth;
1859 unsigned int image_height = image_copy._encodedHeight;
1860 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, codec_type, image_width, image_height] {
1861 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1862 if (codec_type == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP9 &&
1863 send_codec_.VP9()->automaticResizeOn) {
1864 unsigned int expected_width = send_codec_.width;
1865 unsigned int expected_height = send_codec_.height;
1866 int num_active_layers = 0;
1867 for (int i = 0; i < send_codec_.VP9()->numberOfSpatialLayers; ++i) {
1868 if (send_codec_.spatialLayers[i].active) {
1869 ++num_active_layers;
1870 expected_width = send_codec_.spatialLayers[i].width;
1871 expected_height = send_codec_.spatialLayers[i].height;
1872 }
1873 }
1874 RTC_DCHECK_LE(num_active_layers, 1)
1875 << "VP9 quality scaling is enabled for "
1876 "SVC with several active layers.";
1877 encoder_stats_observer_->OnEncoderInternalScalerUpdate(
1878 image_width < expected_width || image_height < expected_height);
1879 }
1880 });
1881
1882 // Encoded is called on whatever thread the real encoder implementation run
1883 // on. In the case of hardware encoders, there might be several encoders
1884 // running in parallel on different threads.
1885 encoder_stats_observer_->OnSendEncodedImage(image_copy, codec_specific_info);
1886
1887 // The simulcast id is signaled in the SpatialIndex. This makes it impossible
1888 // to do simulcast for codecs that actually support spatial layers since we
1889 // can't distinguish between an actual spatial layer and a simulcast stream.
1890 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10520): Signal the simulcast id explicitly.
1891 int simulcast_id = 0;
1892 if (codec_specific_info &&
1893 (codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 ||
1894 codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecH264 ||
1895 codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecGeneric)) {
1896 simulcast_id = encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(0);
1897 }
1898
1899 EncodedImageCallback::Result result =
1900 sink_->OnEncodedImage(image_copy, codec_specific_info);
1901
1902 // We are only interested in propagating the meta-data about the image, not
1903 // encoded data itself, to the post encode function. Since we cannot be sure
1904 // the pointer will still be valid when run on the task queue, set it to null.
1905 DataSize frame_size = DataSize::Bytes(image_copy.size());
1906 image_copy.ClearEncodedData();
1907
1908 int temporal_index = 0;
1909 if (codec_specific_info) {
1910 if (codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP9) {
1911 temporal_index = codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP9.temporal_idx;
1912 } else if (codec_specific_info->codecType == kVideoCodecVP8) {
1913 temporal_index = codec_specific_info->codecSpecific.VP8.temporalIdx;
1914 }
1915 }
1916 if (temporal_index == kNoTemporalIdx) {
1917 temporal_index = 0;
1918 }
1919
1920 RunPostEncode(image_copy, clock_->CurrentTime().us(), temporal_index,
1921 frame_size);
1922
1923 if (result.error == Result::OK) {
1924 // In case of an internal encoder running on a separate thread, the
1925 // decision to drop a frame might be a frame late and signaled via
1926 // atomic flag. This is because we can't easily wait for the worker thread
1927 // without risking deadlocks, eg during shutdown when the worker thread
1928 // might be waiting for the internal encoder threads to stop.
1929 if (pending_frame_drops_.load() > 0) {
1930 int pending_drops = pending_frame_drops_.fetch_sub(1);
1931 RTC_DCHECK_GT(pending_drops, 0);
1932 result.drop_next_frame = true;
1933 }
1934 }
1935
1936 return result;
1937}

1939void VideoStreamEncoder::OnDroppedFrame(DropReason reason) {
1940 switch (reason) {
1941 case DropReason::kDroppedByMediaOptimizations:
1942 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1943 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kMediaOptimization);
1944 break;
1945 case DropReason::kDroppedByEncoder:
1946 encoder_stats_observer_->OnFrameDropped(
1947 VideoStreamEncoderObserver::DropReason::kEncoder);
1948 break;
1949 }
1950 sink_->OnDroppedFrame(reason);
1951 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, reason] {
1952 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1953 stream_resource_manager_.OnFrameDropped(reason);
1954 });
1955}

1957DataRate VideoStreamEncoder::UpdateTargetBitrate(DataRate target_bitrate,
1958 double cwnd_reduce_ratio) {
1959 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
1960 DataRate updated_target_bitrate = target_bitrate;
1961
1962 // Drop frames when congestion window pushback ratio is larger than 1
1963 // percent and target bitrate is larger than codec min bitrate.
1964 // When target_bitrate is 0 means codec is paused, skip frame dropping.
1965 if (cwnd_reduce_ratio > 0.01 && target_bitrate.bps() > 0 &&
1966 target_bitrate.bps() > send_codec_.minBitrate * 1000) {
1967 int reduce_bitrate_bps = std::min(
1968 static_cast<int>(target_bitrate.bps() * cwnd_reduce_ratio),
1969 static_cast<int>(target_bitrate.bps() - send_codec_.minBitrate * 1000));
1970 if (reduce_bitrate_bps > 0) {
1971 // At maximum the congestion window can drop 1/2 frames.
1972 cwnd_frame_drop_interval_ = std::max(
1973 2, static_cast<int>(target_bitrate.bps() / reduce_bitrate_bps));
1974 // Reduce target bitrate accordingly.
1975 updated_target_bitrate =
1976 target_bitrate - (target_bitrate / cwnd_frame_drop_interval_.value());
1977 return updated_target_bitrate;
1978 }
1979 }
1980 cwnd_frame_drop_interval_.reset();
1981 return updated_target_bitrate;
1982}
1983
1984void VideoStreamEncoder::OnBitrateUpdated(DataRate target_bitrate,
1985 DataRate stable_target_bitrate,
1986 DataRate link_allocation,
1987 uint8_t fraction_lost,
1988 int64_t round_trip_time_ms,
1989 double cwnd_reduce_ratio) {
1990 RTC_DCHECK_GE(link_allocation, target_bitrate);
1991 if (!encoder_queue_.IsCurrent()) {
1992 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, target_bitrate, stable_target_bitrate,
1993 link_allocation, fraction_lost, round_trip_time_ms,
1994 cwnd_reduce_ratio] {
1995 DataRate updated_target_bitrate =
1996 UpdateTargetBitrate(target_bitrate, cwnd_reduce_ratio);
1997 OnBitrateUpdated(updated_target_bitrate, stable_target_bitrate,
1998 link_allocation, fraction_lost, round_trip_time_ms,
1999 cwnd_reduce_ratio);
2000 });
2001 return;
2002 }
2003 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
2004
2005 const bool video_is_suspended = target_bitrate == DataRate::Zero();
2006 const bool video_suspension_changed = video_is_suspended != EncoderPaused();
2007
2008 if (!video_is_suspended && settings_.encoder_switch_request_callback &&
2009 encoder_selector_) {
2010 if (auto encoder = encoder_selector_->OnAvailableBitrate(link_allocation)) {
2011 QueueRequestEncoderSwitch(*encoder);
2012 }
2013 }
2014
2015 RTC_DCHECK(sink_) << "sink_ must be set before the encoder is active.";
2016
2017 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << "OnBitrateUpdated, bitrate " << target_bitrate.bps()
2018 << " stable bitrate = " << stable_target_bitrate.bps()
2019 << " link allocation bitrate = " << link_allocation.bps()
2020 << " packet loss " << static_cast<int>(fraction_lost)
2021 << " rtt " << round_trip_time_ms;
2022
2023 if (encoder_) {
2024 encoder_->OnPacketLossRateUpdate(static_cast<float>(fraction_lost) / 256.f);
2025 encoder_->OnRttUpdate(round_trip_time_ms);
2026 }
2027
2028 uint32_t framerate_fps = GetInputFramerateFps();
2029 frame_dropper_.SetRates((target_bitrate.bps() + 500) / 1000, framerate_fps);
2030
2031 EncoderRateSettings new_rate_settings{
2032 VideoBitrateAllocation(), static_cast<double>(framerate_fps),
2033 link_allocation, target_bitrate, stable_target_bitrate};
2034 SetEncoderRates(UpdateBitrateAllocation(new_rate_settings));
2035
2036 if (target_bitrate.bps() != 0)
2037 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_ = target_bitrate.bps();
2038
2039 stream_resource_manager_.SetTargetBitrate(target_bitrate);
2040
2041 if (video_suspension_changed) {
2042 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Video suspend state changed to: "
2043 << (video_is_suspended ? "suspended" : "not suspended");
2044 encoder_stats_observer_->OnSuspendChange(video_is_suspended);
2045 }
2046 if (video_suspension_changed && !video_is_suspended && pending_frame_ &&
2047 !DropDueToSize(pending_frame_->size())) {
2048 int64_t pending_time_us =
2049 clock_->CurrentTime().us() - pending_frame_post_time_us_;
2050 if (pending_time_us < kPendingFrameTimeoutMs * 1000)
2051 EncodeVideoFrame(*pending_frame_, pending_frame_post_time_us_);
2052 pending_frame_.reset();
2053 }
2054}
2055
2056bool VideoStreamEncoder::DropDueToSize(uint32_t pixel_count) const {
2057 if (!stream_resource_manager_.DropInitialFrames() ||
2058 !encoder_target_bitrate_bps_.has_value()) {
2059 return false;
2060 }
2061
2062 bool simulcast_or_svc =
2063 (send_codec_.codecType == VideoCodecType::kVideoCodecVP9 &&
2064 send_codec_.VP9().numberOfSpatialLayers > 1) ||
2065 (send_codec_.numberOfSimulcastStreams > 1 ||
2066 encoder_config_.simulcast_layers.size() > 1);
2067
2068 if (simulcast_or_svc) {
2069 if (stream_resource_manager_.SingleActiveStreamPixels()) {
2070 pixel_count = stream_resource_manager_.SingleActiveStreamPixels().value();
2071 } else {
2072 return false;
2073 }
2074 }
2075
2076 uint32_t bitrate_bps =
2077 stream_resource_manager_.UseBandwidthAllocationBps().value_or(
2078 encoder_target_bitrate_bps_.value());
2079
2080 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::ResolutionBitrateLimits> encoder_bitrate_limits =
2081 GetEncoderInfoWithBitrateLimitUpdate(
2082 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo(), encoder_config_, default_limits_allowed_)
2083 .GetEncoderBitrateLimitsForResolution(pixel_count);
2084
2085 if (encoder_bitrate_limits.has_value()) {
2086 // Use bitrate limits provided by encoder.
2087 return bitrate_bps <
2088 static_cast<uint32_t>(encoder_bitrate_limits->min_start_bitrate_bps);
2089 }
2090
2091 if (bitrate_bps < 300000 /* qvga */) {
2092 return pixel_count > 320 * 240;
2093 } else if (bitrate_bps < 500000 /* vga */) {
2094 return pixel_count > 640 * 480;
2095 }
2096 return false;
2097}
