2116void VideoStreamEncoder::RunPostEncode(const EncodedImage& encoded_image,
2117 int64_t time_sent_us,
2118 int temporal_index,
2119 DataSize frame_size) {
2120 if (!encoder_queue_.IsCurrent()) {
2121 encoder_queue_.PostTask([this, encoded_image, time_sent_us, temporal_index,
2122 frame_size] {
2123 RunPostEncode(encoded_image, time_sent_us, temporal_index, frame_size);
2124 });
2125 return;
2126 }
2127
2128 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&encoder_queue_);
2129
2130 absl::optional<int> encode_duration_us;
2131 if (encoded_image.timing_.flags != VideoSendTiming::kInvalid) {
2132 encode_duration_us =
2133 // TODO(nisse): Maybe use capture_time_ms_ rather than encode_start_ms_?
2134 TimeDelta::Millis(encoded_image.timing_.encode_finish_ms -
2135 encoded_image.timing_.encode_start_ms)
2136 .us();
2137 }
2138
2139 // Run post encode tasks, such as overuse detection and frame rate/drop
2140 // stats for internal encoders.
2141 const bool keyframe =
2142 encoded_image._frameType == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
2143
2144 if (!frame_size.IsZero()) {
2145 frame_dropper_.Fill(frame_size.bytes(), !keyframe);
2146 }
2147
2148 if (HasInternalSource()) {
2149 // Update frame dropper after the fact for internal sources.
2150 input_framerate_.Update(1u, clock_->TimeInMilliseconds());
2151 frame_dropper_.Leak(GetInputFramerateFps());
2152 // Signal to encoder to drop next frame.
2153 if (frame_dropper_.DropFrame()) {
2154 pending_frame_drops_.fetch_add(1);
2155 }
2156 }
2157
2158 stream_resource_manager_.OnEncodeCompleted(encoded_image, time_sent_us,
2159 encode_duration_us);
2160 if (bitrate_adjuster_) {
2161 bitrate_adjuster_->OnEncodedFrame(
2162 frame_size, encoded_image.SpatialIndex().value_or(0), temporal_index);
2163 }
2164}

2170}

2201
2202void VideoStreamEncoder::CheckForAnimatedContent(
2203 const VideoFrame& frame,
2204 int64_t time_when_posted_in_us) {
2205 if (!automatic_animation_detection_experiment_.enabled ||
2206 encoder_config_.content_type !=
2207 VideoEncoderConfig::ContentType::kScreen ||
2208 stream_resource_manager_.degradation_preference() !=
2209 DegradationPreference::BALANCED) {
2210 return;
2211 }
2212
2213 if (expect_resize_state_ == ExpectResizeState::kResize && last_frame_info_ &&
2214 last_frame_info_->width != frame.width() &&
2215 last_frame_info_->height != frame.height()) {
2216 // On applying resolution cap there will be one frame with no/different
2217 // update, which should be skipped.
2218 // It can be delayed by several frames.
2219 expect_resize_state_ = ExpectResizeState::kFirstFrameAfterResize;
2220 return;
2221 }
2222
2223 if (expect_resize_state_ == ExpectResizeState::kFirstFrameAfterResize) {
2224 // The first frame after resize should have new, scaled update_rect.
2225 if (frame.has_update_rect()) {
2226 last_update_rect_ = frame.update_rect();
2227 } else {
2228 last_update_rect_ = absl::nullopt;
2229 }
2230 expect_resize_state_ = ExpectResizeState::kNoResize;
2231 }
2232
2233 bool should_cap_resolution = false;
2234 if (!frame.has_update_rect()) {
2235 last_update_rect_ = absl::nullopt;
2236 animation_start_time_ = Timestamp::PlusInfinity();
2237 } else if ((!last_update_rect_ ||
2238 frame.update_rect() != *last_update_rect_)) {
2239 last_update_rect_ = frame.update_rect();
2240 animation_start_time_ = Timestamp::Micros(time_when_posted_in_us);
2241 } else {
2242 TimeDelta animation_duration =
2243 Timestamp::Micros(time_when_posted_in_us) - animation_start_time_;
2244 float area_ratio = static_cast<float>(last_update_rect_->width *
2245 last_update_rect_->height) /
2246 (frame.width() * frame.height());
2247 if (animation_duration.ms() >=
2248 automatic_animation_detection_experiment_.min_duration_ms &&
2249 area_ratio >=
2250 automatic_animation_detection_experiment_.min_area_ratio &&
2251 encoder_stats_observer_->GetInputFrameRate() >=
2252 automatic_animation_detection_experiment_.min_fps) {
2253 should_cap_resolution = true;
2254 }
2255 }
2256 if (cap_resolution_due_to_video_content_ != should_cap_resolution) {
2257 expect_resize_state_ = should_cap_resolution ? ExpectResizeState::kResize
2258 : ExpectResizeState::kNoResize;
2259 cap_resolution_due_to_video_content_ = should_cap_resolution;
2260 if (should_cap_resolution) {
2261 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Applying resolution cap due to animation detection.";
2262 } else {
2263 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Removing resolution cap due to no consistent "
2264 "animation detection.";
2265 }
2266 main_queue_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, [this,
2267 should_cap_resolution]() {
2268 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(main_queue_);
2269 video_source_sink_controller_.SetPixelsPerFrameUpperLimit(
2270 should_cap_resolution ? absl::optional<size_t>(kMaxAnimationPixels)
2271 : absl::nullopt);
2272 video_source_sink_controller_.PushSourceSinkSettings();
2273 }));
2274 }
2275}
